caption.p: Voltammetry of a CaO 2/O covered (dashed line) and regenerated (solid line) Au (exchange disk) electrode in (20 % O 2+80 % Ar)‐saturated 0.1 m Ca(ClO 4) 2 containing DMSO at 20 mV s −1 and 9 Hz rotation frequency vs Ag/Ag + using a usual H‐cell. The disk current is normalized o the geometrical disk surface area. The disk electrode roughness was f R≈13.
